# 🧠 **1. What is this system? (Simple meaning)**

👉 You are building a system for **collection agents**
👉 They handle **loan recovery cases**

So your system must help agents:

* Track cases
* Add notes
* Follow up
* manage tasks

---

# 🧩 **2. Functional Requirements (What your system MUST DO)**

---

## 📌 **A. Case Management (Main Feature)**

👉 This is the heart of your system

Your system should allow:

* ✅ Create a case
  (Example: customer didn’t pay loan)

* ✅ View case details
  (all info in one screen)

* ✅ Update case status

  ```
  OPEN → IN_PROGRESS → RESOLVED → CLOSED
  ```

* ✅ Set priority

  ```
  LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH
  ```

* ✅ Set case type

  ```
  DELINQUENCY / DISPUTE / HARDSHIP
  ```

---

## 📝 **B. Case Notes**

👉 Agents write what happened

Example:

> “Customer promised to pay next week”

System should:

* Add note
* Show all notes (history)

Each note must store:

* Who wrote it
* When
* What they wrote

---

## 📅 **C. Follow-Up Tasks**

👉 Agents must take actions

Example:

* Call customer
* Visit house

System should:

* Create task
* Assign to agent
* Set due date
* Track status:

  ```
  OPEN / DONE / OVERDUE
  ```

---

## ⚠️ **D. Hardship Handling**

👉 Some customers have real problems

Example:

* Medical emergency
* Job loss

System should:

* Mark hardship
* Store reason
* Track dates

---

## 🔍 **E. Search & Filter**

👉 Agents should easily find cases

Filter by:

* Status
* Priority
* Case type
* Assigned agent

Search by:

* Case ID
* Loan ID

---

## 📊 **F. Dashboard**

👉 Show summary (very important)

Example:

* Total cases
* Open cases
* Overdue tasks
* High priority cases

👉 This helps managers monitor system

---

# 🔐 **3. Security Requirements (Who can do what)**

---

## 👤 Login System

* User must login

---

## 👥 Roles

| Role       | What they can do |
| ---------- | ---------------- |
| AGENT      | Work on cases    |
| SUPERVISOR | Monitor          |
| ADMIN      | Full control     |

---

## 🔒 Rules

* Only authorized users can:

  * Create cases
  * Update cases
  * Assign tasks

---

# ⚡ **4. Non-Functional Requirements (System Quality)**

---

## 🚀 Performance

* API should be fast (< 2 sec)

---

## 📈 Scalability

* Many users can use system at same time

---

## 🔒 Security

* Use JWT
* Encrypt passwords

---

## 📊 Availability

* System should work always (24/7)

---

# 🗄️ **5. Database Requirements**

👉 What data you store

Tables:

* `collection_case` → cases
* `case_note` → notes
* `follow_up_task` → tasks
* `hardship_flag` → hardship
* `user` → login

---

# 🌐 **6. API Requirements (How frontend talks to backend)**

---

## Case APIs

* Create case

```
POST /cases
```

* Get all cases

```
GET /cases
```

* Get one case

```
GET /cases/{id}
```

* Update case

```
PUT /cases/{id}
```

---

## Notes APIs

* Add note

```
POST /notes
```

* Get notes

```
GET /cases/{id}/notes
```

---

## Task APIs

* Create task

```
POST /tasks
```

* Get tasks

```
GET /tasks
```

* Update task

```
PUT /tasks/{id}
```

---

